<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1618,1897]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
REMARKS. The large proportion of black on the head and mesothorax along with the transverse black fascia on the anterior pronotal collar are unique to the species within the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[890,1064,1654,1681]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="501 - 519" refId="ref90929" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2016 c) Generic redescription, two new species, and a key to the species of the cicada genus Ariasa Distant, 1905 with the description of a new genus (Hemiptera: Cicadidae: Cicadinae: Fidicinini). Zootaxa, 4137 (4), 501 - 519. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4137.4. 3" type="journal article" year="2016">Sanborn 2016c</bibRefCitation>
). The species has been associated with the 
<collectingRegion box="[249,321,1690,1716]" country="Argentina" name="Chaco" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Chaco</collectingRegion>
floristic province in 
<collectingCountry box="[554,665,1690,1716]" name="Argentina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, J. E. &amp; Philllips, P. K. &amp; Heath, M. S. &amp; Noriega, F. G." box="[680,916,1690,1716]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="29368" refId="ref91728" refString="Sanborn, A. F., Heath, J. E., Philllips, P. K., Heath, M. S. &amp; Noriega, F. G. (2011 a) Thermal adaptation and diversity in tropical ecosystems: evidence from cicadas (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). PLoS ONE, 6, e 29368. https: // doi. ORG / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0029368" type="journal article" year="2011">
Sanborn 
<emphasis box="[782,838,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2011a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S." box="[927,1191,1690,1716]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref91517" refString="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, M. S. (2014) The cicadas of Argentina with new records, a new genus and fifteen new species (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 3883 (1), 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3883.1. 1" type="journal article" year="2014">Sanborn &amp; Heath 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1618,1897]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
